        Official Singles Chart on 21/1/2022

        21 January 2022 - 27 January 2022

        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        WEEKLY CHART REVIEW (21/01/2022 – 27/01/2022):

        🔴 (Negative)

        1) ‘Waiting For A Lifetime’ appears to have underperformed massively! I was hoping that it would get at least a bit of recognition given how similar this is to ‘If You Really Love Me [How Will I Know]’ by David Guetta & MistaJam, but apparently John Newman trying a similar sound by himself wasn’t anywhere near as successful.

        🟠 (Mixed)

        1) In easily the biggest news of the week, ‘We Don’t Talk About Bruno’ becomes the new #1, which even though I have no strong opinion on it, is a massive moment in history for the Latin musical culture! I’ll admit that it’s tough to review a song from a movie when you’ve not seen the film it’s from itself, but understanding the context of where the character of Bruno lies in ‘Encanto’, I now get why this would be the breakthrough hit (even if they say his name an awful lot for someone who they claim not to discuss). Even outside of that, with as many cast members as possible getting solo parts here, it has a very theatrical & eccentric take to it, which is definitely makes it an amusing listen, but I just have more of a personal connection to the big anthemic & motivational hits when it comes to these kind of musicals. So yeah, it’s still not my favourite track from the soundtrack by any means & I remain completely baffled that of all the Disney classics over the years, this is the one that makes it to #1, but the song has grown on me at least a little over the past week! We’ll see it where it goes from here, but honestly, it doesn’t look the hype is slowing down anytime soon.

        2) As a result of the above, ‘ABCDEFU’ falls from the top spot! It’s unfortunately soured on me a little, but that’s only by too much exposure to the “nicer” version on the radio (which is significantly less sincere than the “angrier” version) rather than anything Gayle’s done as such. Although it’ll be interesting to see how well her new single ‘Ur Just H0rny’ performs in the weeks ahead! No, guys, I’m seriously not making that up, that’s the song title.

        3) Unsurprisingly, ‘Surface Pressure’ is also gathering even further momentum! However, unlike ‘We Don’t Talk About Bruno’, this is song that I’ve been fairly lukewarm on from the start & my opinion on it hasn’t really changed at all. I don’t know about you guys, but I feel that in ‘Encanto’s case, a majority of people are going to see the film purely because of the music centred around it, while with other recent musicals, e.g. ‘The Greatest Showman’, ‘A Star Is Born’, ‘Mamma Mia 2’, ‘Frozen’, etc., a lot more people checked out the full soundtrack after seeing the film, but that doesn’t really seem to be the case with ‘Encanto’! Partly the reason for this is also the increased access to streaming since the turn of the decade & honestly, I think we would’ve been seeing an even bigger album for ‘Encanto’ than we would’ve had for ‘Dawn FM’ without OCC’s rules in place, even if on the flipside, the soundtrack itself is selling far less than you’d expect given all the recent discussion that it’s been generating. Maybe it’s not as hyped as the other aforementioned films here are, especially when you look at the box office figures for it, but as a long-time regular chartwatcher, there’s definitely still that sense of curiosity here to see the film given how unique these kind of songs are compared to others inside the Top 10!

        4) I’m fine with Adele pushing ‘Oh My God’ as the next single, given its early commercial success & relatively quality compared to other tracks on ‘30’, but even then, all the second singles from her previous albums just wipe the floor with this.

        5) While ‘Packs & Potions’ is kind of forgettable & it’s hard to even understand what Hazey’s saying, the tropical beat is certainly unique for this kind of rap song & his Scouse accent makes this stand out from his peers even further.

        6) Even though it didn’t end up relatively high, ‘Eazy’ is still the only notable debut of the week! I’ll say this, The Game & Ye’s rap performances here were definitely above my expectations. The former’s always been one to wear his heart on his sleeve & when you look at the storytelling in his lyrics around the battles he has to face in his life for being in the rap industry, the storytelling makes his part all the more evocative. Of course, like anytime Kanye features on a song, he almost always steals the headlines! That kind of frustrates me when his verse is significantly less memorable & unfortunately far more petty, especially with the shots taken at Pete Davidson, although outside of that line, I can somewhat get his frustration given the trials & tribulations he’s recently had to go through in his own personal life. My larger issue is that sincerity like this deserves far better production than that swampy, frail bass & Michel’le’s vocals mixed into this do the song no justice either because of just how out-of-place they feel in already glitchy production! Overall, I unfortunately don’t see myself revisiting this, but at the same time, I can’t really get mad about it either.

        7) ‘Sweet Talker’ fell back out of the Top 40, but I’m not disappointed about it because it’ll return next week thanks to the new Years & Years album.

        🟢 (Positive)

        1) ‘Peru’ made it into the Top 5! Even if it’s only really here because of Ed, it’s awesome to see another major landmark for Afrobeat hits in the UK & yet, it’s probably better than any single on ‘=’ except ‘Visiting Hours’. Ed’s always been at his most interesting when he explores cultural music (it’s probably why ‘÷’ is my favourite album of his) & while this is far from the best thing he’s hopped on, it has a really chilled vibe to it with just enough chemistry with Fireboy DML to stick the landing!

        2) ‘Where Are You Now’ makes yet another climb! Top 10 for this next week? It’s literally within touching distance of making it, haha.

        3) ‘Down Under’ got another small push! The 1984 original rock smash from Men At Work & the 2021 DnB remix from Luude both work for me, even if they’re entirely different songs.

        4) ‘Make Me Feel Good’ completely exploded by the chart! Yeah, it’s repetitive as , but the retro disco feel to it definitely makes it a standout as far as more recent EDM songs in the charts go.

        5) ‘The Motto’ is back inside the Top 40! A rebound for this perhaps isn’t surprising given how much I’ve been hearing it everywhere lately, but a new peak for it? I didn’t see that part coming, but I’m so happy that it did!

        Have a nice weekend everyone! ❤️
